3 die as Sumatra volcano erupts
Mount Sinabung spews volcanic ash in Karo district of North Sumatra during an eruption on Feb 26 this year. (AFP Photo)
Three people died and four others were critically injured on Saturday after a highly active volcano in western Indonesia erupted violently, shooting hot ash and gases into the atmosphere, an official said.
